$(document).ready(function(){
  $("hide-parent").parent().hide();
});
</script>

Same idea as this, but mine doesn't work:
Hiding parent divs in Jquery
http://jsfiddle.net/uydpesxa/ example here: 

A:

You need to put a period in front of hide-parent since it is a class name selector. Fixed code:
<script>
$(document).ready(function(){
  $(".hide-parent").parent().hide();
});
</script>

Also, in your fiddle, you forgot to pick "jQuery" from the list of libraries. See fixed fiddle here: http://jsfiddle.net/uydpesxa/6/
